"reviewcomment":"Wow! This place is literally a hidden gem...no joke, it&#39;s hidden.   It&#39;s on the backside of the building (not facing Wilshire but rather the parking structure).  You can cut through McDonalds all the way to the back and you will find Deli-In.  It&#39;s closer to the Normandie side of the building directly facing the entrance to Wifit Gym.<br><br>Though this is an asian owned establishment serving latin cuisine, don&#39;t knock it.  The food is incredible, the amount of latin clientele showed me that the place is legit. <br><br>I tried a breakfast burrito with bacon and it was yummy. It had the crispiest hash brown and I&#39;m a sucker anything potato related.  I also read that they had good pupusa&#39;s and thank you yelpers, it was delicious!  If you&#39;ve never tried pupusa&#39;s before, it&#39;s an El Salvadorian pancake like dish - you can get it with meat or simply with bean/cheese which seems to be the best way to go!  <br><br>The service was probably the best part of the whole experiencel and everyone seemed to be a regular.  If you like hole in the walls, great food and good service, check this place out.",
