"reviewcomment":"Two weeks later we are back!!! Enjoyed even more than the first time if possible. TOTAL experience and delight to all senses! And of course, a pleasure to see THE charismatic master chef OyamaSan again.<br><br>We brought 3 bottles of wine for the 3 of us and it was perfect<br>1. 2005 Domaine Jean-Louis Chave Hermitage<br>2. 2009 Marcassin Pinot Noir<br>3. 1996 Chateau Margeaux<br><br>Now the heavenly delights ala Chef Kaz<br>1. Appetizer platter with assorted seafood creations- best of each kind. <br>2. beef carpaccio<br>3. Seared rib eye&amp; throat sashimi~ served with ginger and garlic to accompany<br>4. Beef tartar w apple, pear and quail egg- raw<br>5. More neck sashimi ( this is a rare and small cut) <br>~~~~ the grill comes~~~<br>6. Tongue<br>7. Filet mignon <br>8. Outside skirt<br>9. Inside skirt<br>10. Ribeye<br>11. Skirt<br>... And we got more tongueX2, more short rib/ rib eye, more inside short rib <br><br>Lastly dessert we got and assortment of all the flavors of sorbets and ice creams... All made in house. It&#39;s like picking your favorite child.... You can&#39;t. They are ALL delicious!!!!<br><br>We will soon return!!!!",
