"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/RtGEJlrAFFxwdipdstdn0Q/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"I LOVE PORTOS! I have heard about this place for the longest time and I used to live right by the one in North Hollywood. I can&#39;t believe I had never gone. Mostly just because I was always in a rush and the lines there are pretty outrageous. Depending on time of day I guess, but every time I have gone I have had to wait in a decently sized long line. But let me tell you, it is worth it.<br><br>I love that they serve mojitos as well. I didn&#39;t even know until my friend treated me to one of those heavenly drinks, during one of our lunch date outings. It wasn&#39;t very strong but who cares, I&#39;m not planning on getting plastered at 2 in the afternoon. Anyways, it was real mint and fresh fruit, super refreshing and yummy.<br><br>I love there rum cake here as well. The last time I got it it was really soggy though. But I&#39;m not sure if it was because we didn&#39;t eat it right away. There are these really yummy potato balls, they have meat so vegetarians should avoid. But my husband loves them, he couldn&#39;t stop raving about them after he tried them. <br><br>I love the guava cheese pastries as well as other random treats I tried. They always have fresh bakery items and LOTS of variety so you can pick and choose according to whatever your mood and preference is that day. Enjoy!",
