"rating":"5.0",
"reviewcomment":"I&#39;m cranky &amp; critical. I&#39;ve been to some of the best salons in NYC &amp; Europe and have even then been unhappy with the 3rd or 4th cut and moved on. Nue Studio &amp; cafe, under the insanely talented Todd is simply: The Best.<br><br>From opening the door - it&#39;s a sanctuary. You can get coffee, juice (and I hear beer/wine is on the way...) food and a spot to chill. Everyone there is super nice, interesting and not bitchy the way most high end salons are. Awesome music, art vibe - the kind of spot you want to hang out at.<br><br>The Hair: never before have I been able to say something emotional and abstract (&#34;I want to look like a sexy/creative woman, but still management worthy) and get a perfect haircut. At this point I tell Todd the mood I happen to be in and magically (in almost no time) he&#39;s given me the perfect haircut. Every Single Time! I never get &#34;upsold&#34; product and the prices are insanely low for the quality and talent. <br><br>They&#39;re super accommodating about getting you in (I&#39;m always last minute before events). If I want to go conservative, easy, if I want to go wild -awesome. <br><br>Best hair studio in L.A.",
