"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/RNNrhnQehcq3TuEmjJxquA/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"I&#39;ve eaten my fair of shawarma, falafel and kebabs at 100+ different establishments over the course of my lifetime. I&#39;ve traveled to the Middle East several times. I can say with full confidence, I know my laffa, hummus, tahini et al. And Joe&#39;s knows it best.<br><br>Where to begin? The obvious place is the bowl of fried pita chips sprinkled with zatar at the counter to tie you over until your order is ready. They&#39;re more addictive than french fries -- I dare you to try and eat just one. The owners know it too which is why they provide little containers with a pair of tongs next to the pita chips. <br><br>The laffa is made fresh on the premises and rivals any laffa anywhere. It&#39;s so tasty you can eat it on its own but then you&#39;d miss out on the seasoned shawarma, creamy hummus and lemony fresh salad to wrap in it. That said, I had the shawarma in a laffa today and I&#39;m still reveling in my meal. <br><br>I also want to note how the owners/workers at Joe&#39;s are conscientious good people. I was dining with my toddler and they purposely made our meal quicker than other peoples&#39; meals who were ahead of us in line. Knowing full well that toddlers are ticking time bombs, I found it very sweet of the staff to keep this in mind. In this world where manners are disappearing and very few people even hold doors open for moms and newborn babies, the folks at Joe&#39;s are really genuinely nice people. Given that their food is positively excellent, their conscientiousness is just the cherry on top.",
