"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Yeah, so this place gets four and a half stars, but I&#39;ll just give it 5.  Why? Keep reading...1. Because that was the best damn eggs, toast, n tots I have ever eaten!  Who knew brunch could be so good? 2.The side of smashed tots just put me over the edge.  And forget about it when my friend (who ordered &#39;eggs all over your face&#39;) left the table for the ladies&#39; room, I sure did get her eggs all over MY face.  What was that green sauce?  I don&#39;t know, but it was all over my face. <br><br>#YUM.<br><br>I wasn&#39;t finished yet.  3. I dipped into our other guest&#39;s buckwheat pancake, but more importantly, I basically stole all of her cashew? nut butter and fresh fruit and put it all over my toast. Not my face, weirdo, my toast.  That was the eggs.<br><br>4. Sucking down some Allagash Curieux: a bourbon barrel-aged brew (a hard craft draft to find anywhere!) makes any meal a masterpiece and what made this brunch, and place, exceptional. <br><br>The food here is magnificent, and deserves 5 stars, but since I can&#39;t give it 6 stars, I had to use half of the last star for ambience.  4. A disco ball tv in your restaurant playing, what else on a Sunday Brunch? The Breakfast Club.  5. Games, fun, drinks, some cute bearded manager guy...  Not pretentious, not crazy, just chill.  Good people, good food.  No, I regress, it&#39;s not just good, IT&#39;S GREAT.<br><br>And where else do the employees get to wear awesome metallica inspired shirts as uniforms?  <br><br>yeah, I dig this place. I&#39;ll be back.",
