"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Discovered Gang Nam thru Yelp when I searched for Korean tofu bowl. What?!? A place not in Ktown? This I have to see. <br><br>Came here with my girlfriends for dinner. I used to live in the neighborhood and realized it&#39;s in the former Paddy Rice location. Small dining space, modern decor, with crystal chandeliers and a fridge by the cashier/takeout counter with beverage options. (FYI BYOB). <br><br>The food? It is the bomb. All of us raved as we ate. We ordered spicy pork with mushroom, kimchi and seafood tofu bowl combos but sadly they ran out of jap chae and seafood pancake at 8pm on a Thursday. The 14 banchan offering was generous and has that homemade made-with-love feel. This place trumps BCD or Beverly Soondofu. Our ordered food came piping hot, flavorful and take note as other yelpers warned, spicy means spicy here. Usually I get spicy at BCD and it&#39;s not really spicy. Here I can only handle medium and it&#39;s clearing my sinuses in the best of ways!<br><br>I told the sweet older Korean lady serving us that we&#39;ll definitely be back. That was Thursday. I&#39;m going back today (Sat) for takeout! Service is a little slow (small crew?) and they close early at 9pm/Sundays but this is a sweet local business and def worthy of patience and regular support! Go Yelpers Go!",
