"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/5xEzCGYXZbiWhBQXTrWnVw/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Healthyca is my current favorite place to get my salad fix. I work in Burbank and live in the Valley so location-wise, this place is awesome. Parking is street-only but that&#39;s not usually a problem when I go (around 6PM).<br><br>Speaking of awesome, let&#39;s talk salad. I am a prolific salad-eater (I love meat too, don&#39;t get me wrong, but I&#39;ve always loved a hearty salad) and had been looking for a place that does salad right for ages. I have to give Healthyca 5 stars on all points: volume, freshness, composition, dressing. In fact, their salads are so volume-y, if I&#39;m not starving when I start in on one, I sometimes have to save about a third of it to finish later. My favorites are the Avocado Caprese and the Chinese Chicken. I&#39;ve tried every salad except for the Ratatouille and  the Albacore, and they&#39;ve all been good except the Chilled Orient, which was just okay because the soba noodles were a little soggy (maybe because I always take it to go, they get soggy by the time I get home? I suppose I could always just cook up some soba of my own). <br><br>For the side, I always get the Quinoa salad, which is flavorful and, hey, quinoa can do no wrong, right?<br><br>The last time I got the Noho Sausage which was also tasty, and made me want to try some of their hot dishes. <br><br>I was disappointed to find that they changed their hours; they now close at 7PM instead of 9PM which makes it a little harder for me to go there with friends. But, it doesn&#39;t keep me from ordering from my office and picking up on my way home. There&#39;s not a whole lot of seating anyway so be warned, it&#39;s not a fancy sit-down kind of restaurant. But the food is excellent, and that&#39;s what counts!<br><br>Please stay in business forever!!!!!",
