"reviewcomment":"BEST KOREAN BBQ IN KOREATOWN!!!<br><br>the place seems a little ghetto at first, but the inside the restaurant is actually very very clean and nice.<br><br>I was here with my family this Saturday and we ordered the combo B with japchae and dolsot bibimpa, which were SO DELICIOUS. <br><br>combo B comes with marinated beef galbi, prime rib eye steak, pork neck, and another regular beef galbi.  The meat was fresh and had the right amount of fat, which I really liked. The rib eye was awesome as it was a medium sized thick slab of meat.  <br><br>one thing I really like about this place is the service.<br>the friendly hostess was able to sit us in a reasonable time, even though we had a page of people waiting before us. the waiters are all super friendly and nice. when we asked for more banchans/waters/napkings/etc, they actually provided us with a genuine smile. You dont&#39; really get that kind of service in ktown kbbq restaurants.<br><br>you can street park, but the valet parking is only $2.<br><br>ooh also, they have  WOOD FIRE BBQ PIT, which makes this place eve more awesome!",
