"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/4pqVGQ7zv5WULtdaAoICzQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"My buddy Neto had taken me out to lunch a couple of years ago to their previous location on Lakewood Blvd...but Today I finally got a chance to stop by and try this location. <br>Wifey was in the mood for some seafood...something refreshing &amp; light.<br><br>OMG. I was overwhelmed by their menu...my eyes couldn&#39;t keep up with my brain &amp; stomach at the same time. I just asked the guy behind the register &#34;What do you recommend?&#34; He suggested to get a sampler plate, it consist of three mini tostadas. He asked &#34;which three of the fifteen would you like to try?&#34; We went with Mariquita, Mango and the Zombie. <br>Trippy names but great flavors.<br><br>The Mariquita tostada  is shrimp ceviche topped off with the Chef&#39;s peanut/walnut sauce.<br> Zombie tostada is fish ceviche with &#34;Zombie sauce.&#34; <br>The mango tostada is shrimp ceviche, mango, carrot sauce and habanero.<br><br>The empanadas de camaron were large and very tasty especially with that green sauce.<br>The Vida Loca tacos were interesting...fried tacos stuffed with potato and shrimp with a side of seafood consome.<br><br>Anywhere we go and where they serve camarones aguachiles...I have to try them. I was impressed with them freshness and flavor of the shrimps in the green sauce.<br><br>If you know me...I rarely order dessert...But today we had to. They suggested the Capirotada...not overly sweetened... It was just right.<br><br>I must comeback and try the strawberry &amp; honey shrimp ceviche.",
