"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"My husband and I stopped in today to see what the Yelp hype was all about.  First off, we were greeted right away which is a plus in my book. The gentlemen which I assumed was the manger was super accommodating and asked us if we had been to Cilantro before and let us know how everything works. <br><br>We ended up getting the Asada fries which were pretty delicious. We also ordered some chicken and asada tacos. Very tasty meats.  What I love is that I am able to add whatever I want to my tacos. Most Mexican fast food joints always add the same thing to their tacos....onion, salsa &amp; cilantro. I don&#39;t eat two of these three condiments. The homemade pesto&#39;s were impressive...very tasty. Most of the condiments offered were impressive.<br><br>I also tried the sweetened lime and agua fresca drinks. Unfortunately, the agua fresca was too watered down. I should have taken a sip while I was still there. I&#39;m sure it was delicious when it was freshly made but late in the afternoon the ice pretty much watered it down. Aside from this, everything was very yummy and we will definitely be back.",
