"reviewcomment":"Wow! Every fish I tried melted in my mouth like butter.   It&#39;s Omakase Style, for those of you that don&#39;t know, you walk in and just tell the Chef what you don&#39;t like so he doesn&#39;t use that specific thing while creating the sushi pieces his way and surprises you with his genius creations.   They will not do Specialty rolls or California Rolls here, this place is the real deal.   This is definitely one of my new favorite Sushi places.  Yay!   <br><br>It is in a strip mall and it is really small inside but the service is excellent and  the fish is as fresh as it is going to get. I love that he uses very little rice when making that beautiful piece of fish sit on top- you have to wonder if there&#39;s rice under it.  Freshly made Wasabi too- which I barely used there was no need.   He did a smoked Salmon and regular Salmon side by side with this thin (tape) looking piece on top that had a tab bit of sweet flavor to it...Geez it was phenomenal.  My taste buds was gripping that thing in the most delightful way. <br><br> We got 4 plates each with two pieces on each plate for $100.  For amazing sushi so worth it.   If you love real sushi you will love and appreciate this place. This place isn&#39;t for those that love those big specialty rolls covered in mayo sauce.",
