"reviewcomment":"Staying two blocks away for a business trip, so wandered in my first night in Beverly Hills for dinner. Was lucky to get a seat at the bar counter. It was a Monday night, and it was packed. Good sign.<br><br>I ordered a Negroni while deciding what to eat. Note to bartender, a proper Negroni is stirred, no shaken. But not the end of the world.<br><br>I ordered the chicken sandwich and the fries. The fries were perfectly cooked, and came with both ketchup and a spicy mayo for dipping. And I liked that they brought them out quickly without waiting for the sandwich to be done. The chicken sandwich was very good, definitely among the better chicken sandwiches I&#39;ve had. But in the ranking of exciting things to eat, I have to admit chicken sandwiches are not high on my personal list. So while tasty, I couldn&#39;t help but stare and be jealous of the great looking hamburger served to the guy down the counter. I had to come back!<br><br>So went back the next day for lunch, ordered the kale salad to start, and the hamburger. The kale salad was perfectly prepared. Extremely tasty. The hamburger, I must admit, was among the best I&#39;ve had in a long, long time. Something about all the elements really working together to create an exceptional sandwich - the meat, the cole slaw, just the right amount of the secret sauce, mayo, pickle. Delicious.",
