"reviewcomment":"Seafood from a taco truck are you crazy!!! Yeah thats what I said... turns out its actually very very very good!<br><br>When I think of having seafood the last thing that comes to mind is having seafood from a lunch truck- UNTIL now.  Rolling up to 4th and Rose isn&#39;t much of a view and the location isn&#39;t on a main stretch of Venice beach but it adds to the mystique of it all.  The few times Ive been here its been pretty busy but the line and wait are quick, people are friendly, and food is definitely good eats!<br><br>My all time favorite thing to order here is the tostada de ceviche- finely minced fish, tomato, cilantro and onion on a crispy tostada, with a slice of freshly sliced avocado. Its fresh, its light, and seasoned perfectly!  Its just a great snack especially on a warm day.  <br><br>The tacos here are pretty good as well.  The tacos de asada is pretty standard. The meat is nicely cooked, juicy and seasoned well. The tacos de chicharron are really good.  Nice and fried, seasoned and delicious.  Tacos are served with pinto beans but you can opt out.  The salsa isn&#39;t very spicy and does need a little salt but still pretty good compared to other salsa I&#39;ve had.  <br><br>Overall, the snacks here are simple but oh so good.  Try it then become a regular like me!",
