"reviewcomment":"This is where I first tried Moroccan cuisine, and I became hooked. <br>The atmosphere is dark and very small, but I imagine it&#39;s what gives it its authentic &amp; cozy charm.<br><br>As always, we did the tasting menu. <br><br>The Sangria was one of the best I&#39;ve ever had; it&#39;s quite phenomenal.<br><br>Hummus<br>It comes with marinated olives and berber bread. It was nice, but nothing special.<br><br>Tomato &amp; Cucumber Tartare<br>Refreshing palette cleanser!<br><br>Bastilla<br>This dish brought me to tears because I realized I can&#39;t eat this everyday. I love anything with phyllo, but cornish hen, scrambled eggs &amp; chocolate together??? Surprisingly AMAZING explosion of flavor bursts in your mouth every time. This is a must order dish.<br><br>Sea Bass Tagine<br>It was nice, but not memorable.<br><br>Lamb Chops<br>Meat seasoned and cooked to perfection. It was very juicy and my husband loved this the best.<br><br>Chocolate Soup<br>Yummy! I loved how it wasn&#39;t overly sweet :)<br><br>While everything made my tastebuds happy, I think I&#39;ll skip the tasting menu next time and just order like 7 of the Bastilla. It&#39;s the most unique and stand out dish that ranks among my top 10 favorite dishes. I don&#39;t know how I can survive without having Bastilla from Tagine on a regular basis. This makes me want to cry.",
