"reviewcomment":"Thank you Yelp! for helping me find this place! Over the the last several months it has become one of my favorite spots in the valley. :)<br><br>My favorite sandwich (although they&#39;re all delicious!) is the Imported Prosciutto Sandwich-- Caprese style (with fresh mozzarella, basil and tomatoes instead of the traditional deli toppings) on their giant freshly made ciabatta bread. The sandwich drizzled with balsalmic vinegar and a little olive oil. Swoon! To die for! You have the option for domestic or imported prosciutto for a few extra bucks. Splurge a little on the imported. Trust me. It&#39;s worth it! <br><br>This place not only has fantastical sandwiches but they&#39;re a Mecca for all things Italian as far as your kitchen and stomach are concerned. From fig jams to truffle oil, blood orange sparking water and hazelnut chocolates...all homemade pastas, breads, sauces and desserts. They&#39;re phenomenal! They even have dishes like homemade Butternut Squash ravioli that they&#39;ve hand packaged and stuck in their freezer section for an easy &#34;homemade&#34; Italian meal. You just can&#39;t go wrong. You can order hot food here or take it home to cook later. Plus its been around for decades and has the sweet old school charm I just adore. Some days a cute 85-year-old man, who I assume is the owner, sits at a table by the window just sipping on a coffee and watching the comings and goings of his shop. . Major hearts for this place.",
