"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/8ED_LHJz1GZit1nIPLyDsw/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Came here last Sunday on the 23rd for my birthday brunch with my lady friends.  I live in Newport Beach but had my girls come in from San Diego and SF for the weekend celebration of my life.  We were staying nearby and had been yelping brunch spots and this one was so near us and about a 10min walk.  (Sidenote: I had even considered coming here for dinner and drinks the previous Friday but it just didn&#39;t work out because you can&#39;t get 6 girls ready in time to go anywhere.)<br><br>Anyway, we had made reservations and were quickly seated by the owner, Martin.  We were seated upstairs, which gave a bit more intimate feel that I loved.  The day was sunny and warm, couldn&#39;t have asked for a better day to brunch.  Martin was such a sweetheart, he brought us out champagne, OJ and a bottle of rosé cava (which he topped off our mimosas with) and they looked just beautiful.  Worthy of Instagram.  He suggested different plates for us to try and we loved all of them.  <br>  -Jalepeño Yellowtail: so fresh and flavorful, we had to get 3 orders.<br>  -Chicken and Waffles: again, we got 2 orders to share and even another order of just the chicken.  Finger lickin&#39; good.<br>  -Breakfast Quiche: so soft and fluffy, spinach blend that melts in your mouth with a flaky, buttery crust.  <br>  -Eggs Benedict, Chipotle Scrambled Egg Tostada: didn&#39;t try either of those, but they looked fab.<br><br>The mimosas kept a&#39;flowin and the staff was incredibly sweet and helpful.  I had an amazing time here and will be back again!  The only thing I can say is that the music selection was a little off, a DJ would have been cool to have, but I&#39;m not sure if this particular part of the neighborhood would allow such thing for Sunday Brunch.  Maybe I just wanted to hear party music cause of my birthday mood.  Nonetheless, I had a spectacular time here!  The owner Martin seemed busy running the place but always made sure to check on our party and the rest of the staff were very accommodating.  Until next time!",
