"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/dlIQZQmV3eAsA03BHlgDAA/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"I was at a friends office in Torrance one day and could smell something really good!  He told me he had some soul food from a place in LA.  He didn&#39;t remember the name of the restaurant but remembered the area he bought it from.  Based on what he had told me, it wasn&#39;t too far from my church.  Sunday morning, my Mom said she wanted to find the restaurant and so we did!  I logged into Yelp and did a local search from soul food.  Several restaurants came up but this one had an address near the location my friend had described.  <br><br>We find the location, see a lady walking through the parking lot heading towards the restaurant.  My Mom asked her if she&#39;s eaten here before and she said she comes every week.  We get out, go in to take a look and decide to stay and give it a try.  We&#39;re so so glad we did!  We ordered the smothered pork chops, mashed potatoes, cabbage, macaroni &amp; cheese and buttered corn.  Oh my were we pleasantly pleased!  <br><br>While eating, our amazing server along with other staff members came by our table to make sure we were taken care of.  One of the people that stopped by was &#34;Grandpa&#34; - i was later told he&#39;s the youngest son of the owner.  He along with the other staff members were very friendly with all the customers.  Our server later brought out a banana pudding and peach cobbler - compliments of Grandpa for my Mom&#39;s birthday.  As if that wasn&#39;t enough, Grandpa told the lady at the table next to us (Ms. Cookie - also the lady from the parking lot) that the cookies were in the oven.  She looks at us and says &#34;don&#39;t leave, you have to have cookies with Ms. Cookie.&#34;  Shortly thereafter,  a server  brought over two containers of fresh baked Oatmeal Raisin Chocolate Chip cookies - they were AWESOME!!!<br><br>As if we needed anything else to make us love this place ... there was more.  One of the customers was and elderly man.  When he finished his food, a server called a cab for him as he had taken the bus to the restaurant.  Grandpa had them cancel the cab and Grandpa drove him home - that&#39;s customer service at it&#39;s finest!  <br><br>We&#39;ll definitely be eating at this restaurant again!  Thanks for a great experience Mama Joan&#39;s Soul Food!!!",
