"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/5lCSfCoo2pAEaagfPUQDrQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Eating at Fork in the Road is a truly incredible experience. Four of us went early the night of the Academy Awards and expected to be there for an hour and a half, but ended up staying for 3 hours! The staff was warm and friendly. May Ling was our waitress; she  had a great personality and couldn&#39;t have been more helpful. She had a detailed knowledge of the menu and was a great guide for each of us. Drew, the chef, was remarkably accessible and open. His passion and creativity were on display for every dish he created. <br><br>For small plates, we had the green beans, tabouli with naan, ratatouille, and a broccoli with micro lettuces (which flowers twice a year). All were exceptional. For entrees we had capellini with cheese and tomatoes, chicken with parmesan fritters, beef brisket with root vegetables, and lamb osso bucco. Each dish was distinctive and visually inspired. For dessert we had 3 ice creams: lavendar mint, white chocolate, and a hot chocolate that was cold in the dish but had a spicy kick when it went down your throat. We also had a berry dish which was also delicious. <br><br>Eating at Fork in the Road was like a dream that we didn&#39;t want to wake up from.<br>We can&#39;t wait to return.",
