"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Amazing!  From the moment we walked in we were greeted by the owner who made all sorts of wonderful meal recommendations.  You can plainly see that this restaurant owner loves what he does and lives to make people happy.  He surprised us with an array of sliders of all different types of exotic meats from kangaroo to red deer to wagyu to camel.  The wagyu slider was my favorite along with the zucchini sticks.  The sauces were really delicious and made a great burger an excellent one.  I really liked the wasabi mayo and cranberry mayo the best!  <br><br>Mark, the owner, checked on us frequently and made sure we had a comfortable, enjoyable, perfect dining experience.  It is a rarity to experience that high level of attentiveness and customer service these days, especially in L.A.  <br><br>This restaurant was made for good, kind, friendly people to enjoy some delicious comfort food and engage (or not) in some pleasing conversation with whoever you&#39;re dining with and possibly the owner (he&#39;s a people person who will get you laughing out loud if you let him).   Entitled, pretentious folks need not frequent this establishment as you may be overwhelmed by the fact that respect, decency, and good old-fashioned manners are quite common (and encouraged) at Peas &amp; Carrots.<br><br>I&#39;m so excited to take my friends here!  Thank you, Mark, for your hospitality and comfort food.  You&#39;re a fabulous human being.",
