"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Love everything about this place!<br>The ambiance was absolutely lovely.  Trendy and upscale but not pretentious.  The staff, with the exception of our actual server, were all extremely helpful.<br><br>Now the most important part: the food.  Everything we had was delicious.  And the menu had so many different options.  I wish we had larger appetites so we could have tried more items.<br><br>Brussels sprouts: best i&#39;ve ever had.  And the best part is that there was no bacon in them.  As someone who doesn&#39;t eat pork, I&#39;m often frustrated when every brussels sprout dish on ever menu has bacon but this one didn&#39;t and it was delicious.<br><br>Moussaka: second best I&#39;ve ever had, only to the moussaka I had in Santorini.  Very light and delicate which is almost impossible for this type of dish.<br><br>Scallops: also really delicious.  Well prepared and came with the perfect sauce.<br><br>Chicken and duck bastilla: this one I didn&#39;t like as much.  It was too acidic for my taste.  I expected a bastilla to be a lot sweeter than this one was.<br><br>Sticky toffee pudding: everything about this was yummy.  It&#39;s not an overly ambitious or sophisticated dessert.  It&#39;s gooey and warm and kind of along the lines of comfort food. Definitely yummy.<br><br>I can&#39;t wait to come here again to try other menu items.  Also I would say this is a great place for vegetarians as there were a lot of meatless options.",
