"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/juqveEGPptuUtcBXIjXMdQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"I&#39;m seriously warning you, do not, I repeat, DO NOT go with a group! Tapas restaurants are the new and in lately, but I tend to be disappointed at the meager portions. Just charge me more and give me something satisfying! Us six girls potentially had the saddest yet the most scrumptious meal because their portions were so tiny, yet their dishes so delicious. [See photo of tiny popcorn bacons below and imagine it being shared by 6 girls]. It also did not help that the dishes all came out one by one...<br><br>Moving onto the food, which was *to die for*!<br><br>1. Popcorn bacon - creative dish, but we basically paid $8 for salty tater tots the size of a ketchup dish. Not sure why everyone else on Yelp is raving abt it.<br>2. Brussels sprout hash - delish, but what kind of establishment dOesn&#39;t have good brussels sprouts? But I really want to give Black Hogg credit for their creativity. The chef added over easy eggs to this dish to give it a twist.<br>3. Pork belly tacos - my eyes were the size of saucers after that delicious first bite. But imagine 6 ppl sharing 4 tacos lolol. #sad <br>4. Roast mushroom brioche box - the best dish of the night along w the pork belly tacos! Mushrooms on brick toast? Yes pls.<br>5. 53rd and 6th lamb and rice - nice try, but this tastes nothing like the 53rd and 6th chicken and rice in NYC. It was very... cilantro-y...<br>6. Jerk chicken &amp; coconut rice - what a pair made in heaven, and the chicken was so juicy!<br>7. Five leches bread pudding - pecans, salty vanilla ice cream.. it was gone in seconds.<br><br>Trendy, yummy, and reservations are a must. Go with a significant other, or 2 friends max, and you&#39;ll have an amazing time!",
