"reviewcomment":"I was half expecting a long juicy bratwurst in a tiny, dense bun (like the street vendors serve in good old Europe) but these are cut up in bite sized pieces, seasoned to your choice level of spice, topped with curry sauce and served with a couple of pieces of classic German bread. You get the all the good tastes of the curry wurst experience without the mess of the juices falling down your face and all over your hands-it was kind of perfect,  really. Add the crunchy, salty fritten and you got yourself a hefty snack. Don&#39;t be shy with the mayo - yes, mayonnaise - because as weird as it may seem putting it on your fritten, it actually cuts the salt and suddenly you can&#39;t stop eating it. Plus,  that&#39;s how they do it in good old Europe. <br><br>Back to the wursts, We tried beef and pork,  both were good. Doubt any of the options are bad. And definitely affordable.",
