"reviewcomment":"One of the more memorable meals I&#39;ve had recently.<br><br>Rolled in here on a Saturday night around 8 pm without reservations.  Was seated immediately.  The restaurant is classy but not pretentious.  Cozy setting, decorated well with cute little giraffes perched above on the ledges.  A big glass window with a view of the street.<br><br>They started us with some soft tasty bread, and I dabbled myself with a glass of crisp white wine.  Ordered the sauteed wild pacific shrimp salad.  SO AMAZING.  Some of the best shrimp I&#39;ve ever had.  They were gigantic and meaty, when I bit into them they exploded with flavor.  They were grilled and had that slight charred flavor with some citric to it.  Tons of texture, had to actually chew them to digest cuz they were so big.  Came with some arugula, shaved fennel, white beans, raisins, and olive lemon vinaigrette.  A spectacular salad.  My girl got the angus filet and she practically orgasmed eating it.  I sampled it and it was indeed tender and delicious.  Some nice potato gratin with it.<br><br>We finished with a sticky toffee pudding that blew our minds.  Came with some vanilla ice cream.  Don&#39;t even know what to say about this, it was just great.  With two glasses of wine and all that it was a very reasonable tab.  Service was excellent all night, and the atmosphere was warm.  Food was spectacular, I will certainly be returning to JiRaffe.",
