"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"I live in San Diego. I did a roadtrip to LA with my GF to eat. I found this place on Yelp and went out of our way to go to downtown LA at 10pm in the evening. We parked about 4 blocks away and walked passed many homeless people, even 2 guys that were sharing a tent, to get here and try a burger. The game plan was for us to share a burger as we had dinner earlier in the evening. Also to share some cheesey tots as they look amazing in the photos. Unfortunately, we stuck to this plan and I only had half a Black Sheep burger. This burger was amazing and cemented the fact that LA has such an elevated food scene compared to SD. The cheesey tots were good but unmemorable because of the spotlight of this damn tasty burger.<br><br>So, is this place worth a 2 hour drive, a half mile walk past some dangerous street residents? Yes. Yes it is. My only complaint was that the burger was too small, but even if it was a 2 pound burger, I&#39;d probably still have the same complaint. But seriously, the burger was on the small side.<br><br>Black Sheep, I will be seeing you soon!",
