"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/QYv7LvaoyuaEJRDRpPtFDQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"My roommate and I came here to &#34;celebrate&#34; her breakup. Really we came to get out of the house and cheer her up a bit, but Doc made sure to turn it into a celebration. He introduced her to Fireball and chatted with us before going to make our lamb chops. <br><br>Speaking of lamb chops, my mouth and mind cannot handle the memory of its goodness. It is 8:53am and I am ready to eat it again. And again. And again. <br><br>We also had the shrimp and grits, and chicken and waffle sliders. Both were delicious, but I have decided I cannot live without the former. It was perfection. <br><br>All the dishes we got were $16. I think that&#39;s totally reasonable considering  how happy me, my mouth, and my stomach were upon departure. I also strongly believe one should eat local, so I&#39;m a huge fan. <br><br>Great staff. Doc is the real deal. The fact that he does some of the cooking makes me like the place even more. He deserves the Best Small Business Owner Award of the Western Hemisphere. Yes, it&#39;s real. You can look it up. <br><br>Don&#39;t look it up. But do go become a regular of the Red Door. <br><br>Entry to the place is in the alley directly behind the street. Look for the glowing red light above the door. Creepy, yes. But you will be so happy you crossed over into wonderland.",
