"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/194zjRxxARvhT-_bUaAh4g/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Came here on a Friday night for dinner and ended up having a blast. We came with a party of eight and we honestly ordered half off the menu. <br><br>We ordered: a Gigantic Bavarian Pretzel (a MUST! Everyone loved the mustard it came with, but it was equally delicious plain), Calamari (perfect ratio of calamari to breading,  Bread and Potato Dumplings (I have to give the bread dumplings the edge here), Wurstplate (pretty big portion, definitely something to share with the table) roasted pork shank for 2 (makes a good appetizer for a large party. The skin was crispy and not too salty, reminded me a bit of roasted duck for some reason). I ordered the Chicken Vesuvio for my entree, it&#39;s chicken breast in a garlic/white wine sauce and comes with potatoes, spinach, red cabbage, and a few brussel sprouts and slices of carrots. <br><br>Dessert: fresh baked cookies (the meringue and truffle were SO good), I also got the sorbet sampler. It came with sour cream sorbet, which I was hesitant to eat, but it was surprisingly yummy. Highly recommended. <br><br>The vibe here is casual, friendly, and the food is delicious. Plus, it got a thumbs up from my German friend. The chef came out to talk to our table, made some recommendations, and then went to the front to sing a few songs with the guy playing keyboard/accordion.  It was so cute I found myself swaying along (and I swear I was sober). Come here with the friends you feel comfortable to stuff your face around, you&#39;ll want to eat without judgment when you&#39;re shoveling that yummy food down, trust me. <br><br>Note: This restaurant has valet--it&#39;s located in a small alley between the restaurant and the business next to it. You&#39;ll see a small sign with &#34;STOP&#34; symbol on it, that&#39;s for the valet.",
