"reviewcomment":"Given the current state of affairs in Jamaica in regards to the rights of homosexuals, and the high level of stigma in Jamaican culture towards gays and lesbians, an educated gay social worker would naturally be mindful in an environment where four seemingly recent Jamaican transplants to LA are speaking in thick patois. Despite my internal nervousness, which was based on my own countertransference, service here is quaint and I believe the men take pride in the food they serve. The environment is seedy to those who might not have grown up in the hood, but for me, this was home. My bf, on the other hand, was a bit nervous.<br><br>I wanted jerk chicken, and the bf wanted oxtail. I also wanted patties. OMG patties. I also craved a bottle of Ting. I wanted it all to go.<br><br>I got everything I wanted. As the food came out, a gentleman opened the containers and showed us the presentation of what I can only describe as the most obscene food porn. It looked so amazing that I immediately felt like I should be slut shamed. When we got home and opened our boxes, the magic continued. Let me tell you: The food is phenomenal.<br><br>You can taste the scotch bonnet peppers in the jerk chicken sauce, and the chicken was smoked beautifully. The vegetables served on the side were also smoky and well seasoned - - also cooked perfectly. The rice was fragrant with coconut, and each element of the plate just complemented the others. I also tried my bf&#39;s oxtail, and it fell off the bone. The gravy was made perfectly... I seriously can&#39;t stop raving about how amazing our dinner was.<br><br>Their beef patties, btw, are exquisite.<br><br>Someone in this restaurant takes exceptional pride in preparation and presentation, and I HIGHLY recommend this restaurant to anyone that appreciates such craftsmanship. <br><br>I don&#39;t think I&#39;ve had better Caribbean food. I can&#39;t wait to go back and bring my friend from NYC that has been stuck out here for two years without the magic of the Caribbean. I&#39;ll be a good friend by reminding her to bring a change of panties.",
