"reviewcomment":"Total hole in the wall restaurant, and there&#39;s a bit of a wait during peak hours, but omg. The food is so good ! I&#39;ve been to at least 15 different Thai restaurants, and this one is something special. I came with 3 other people and we ordered: <br><br>#1 (hoy kha) medium spicy: their medium is definitely more like extra spicy. But it&#39;s not the burn your tongue off so you can&#39;t taste anything else spicy.. The broth was extremely delicious ! <br><br>#2 (Boat noodles) mild: perfect amount of kick. Delicious broth, noodles were perfect (we got egg noodles for all of our noodle dishes) <br><br>Duck noodle soup: best I&#39;ve ever had. Most duck noodle soups are too sweet for my taste, but this one was perfect ! <br><br>Crispy pork with Chinese broccoli: pretty good ! <br><br>We also got some kind of sausage appetizer that comes with cabbage  to wrap it in, and fresh garlic, ginger, and some kind of spicy pepper. Very flavorful and good to eat as a side ! <br><br>The Thai tea was delicious as well (of course) <br><br>One other thing I love about this place is that you can order a small sized bowl of noodles for only 3.95 versus a large bowl. This is a great option if you&#39;re not super hungry or if you want to order more than one thing so you can have a variety!",
